## 测试单主键包含group-by, order-by, having
EXPLAIN select sum(A.b), min(B.b), max(C.b)
          from t1 as A, t1 As B, t1 as C
          where A.a = B.a and B.a = C.a
          group by B.b
          having min(B.b) > 0
          order by max(C.b);
Query Plan
===================================================
|ID|OPERATOR           |NAME|EST.ROWS|EST.TIME(us)|
---------------------------------------------------
|0 |MERGE GROUP BY     |    |2       |3           |
|1 |└─SORT             |    |4       |3           |
|2 |  └─TABLE FULL SCAN|A   |4       |3           |
===================================================
Outputs & filters:
-------------------------------------
  0 - output([T_FUN_SUM(A.b)], [A.b], [A.b]), filter(nil), rowset=16
      group([A.b]), agg_func([T_FUN_SUM(A.b)])
  1 - output([A.b]), filter(nil), rowset=16
      sort_keys([A.b, ASC])
  2 - output([A.b]), filter([A.b > 0]), rowset=16
      access([A.b]), partitions(p0)
      is_index_back=false, is_global_index=false, filter_before_indexback[false], 
      range_key([A.a]), range(MIN ; MAX)always true
select sum(A.b), min(B.b), max(C.b)
          from t1 as A, t1 As B, t1 as C
          where A.a = B.a and B.a = C.a
          group by B.b
          having min(B.b) > 0
          order by max(C.b);
+----------+----------+----------+
| sum(A.b) | min(B.b) | max(C.b) |
+----------+----------+----------+
|        2 |        1 |        1 |
|        6 |        3 |        3 |
+----------+----------+----------+
